HEADWORD: Colliquefaction
<hw>Col*liq`ue*fac"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>colliquefactus</ets> melted; <ets>col-</ets> +
<ets>liquefacere</ets>; <ets>liqu⟦emac⟧re</ets> to be liquid +
<ets>facere</ets> to make.]</ety> <def>A melting together; the reduction
of different bodies into one mass by fusion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The incorporation of metals by simple
<qex>colliquefaction</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Collish</ent>⟦br⟧
